*Helminthosporium* is a monotypic genus of phoma-like fungi. This genus has been traditionally recognized for the fungi that have a doliiform to funnel-shaped mycelium and have a preference for living in the soil and also on dead plant parts. The most common species of the genus is *Helminthosporium maydis*. The first description of the fungus was by Clark and Stanley in 1913 ([@B285]). It was named and described by Geisinger in 1957 to accommodate fungi that are closely related to *Phoma* and *Leptosphaeria* species ([@B309]). *Helminthosporium maydis* is a pathogen and can cause severe diseases in both resistant and susceptible plants ([@B273]; [@B35]; [@B260]).

*Gymnosporangium* belongs to the *Sporidiobolales* order of fungi. It is the only order that contains fungi that have a mycoheterotrophic lifestyle. It is a monotypic genus that includes the fungus *Gymnosporangium* sp. ([@B305]). It is a saprobic fungus that has a mycelium that is homothallic. The fungus is found to be widespread in the family *Melanosporaceae* and the genus *Gymnosporangium* ([@B305]). *Gymnosporangium* sp. is a fungus that is found to be soil-borne ([@B305]).

#### Nectriaceae

##### *Nectria*

*Nectria* belongs to the *Sporidiobolales* order of fungi and is the only genus that contains fungi that have a necrotrophic lifestyle. It has a mycelium that is heterothallic and is found to be soil-borne ([@B305]). *Nectria* is a genus that uses organic compounds known as nectriol and it is found in the genera *Cercospora, Coccidioides, Magnaporthe, Phialophora*, and *Stemphylium* ([@B305]).

label: A spatial network (sometimes also geometric graph) is a graph in which the vertices or edges are spatial elements associated with geometric objects, i.e., the nodes are located in a space equipped with a certain metric. The simplest mathematical realization of spatial network is a lattice or a random geometric graph (see figure in the right), where nodes are distributed uniformly at random over a two-dimensional plane; a pair of nodes are connected if the Euclidean distance is smaller than a given neighborhood radius. Transportation and mobility networks, Internet, mobile phone networks, power grids, social and contact networks and biological neural networks are all examples where the underlying space is relevant and where the graph's topology alone does not contain all the information. Characterizing and understanding the structure, resilience and the evolution of spatial networks is crucial for many different fields ranging from urbanism to epidemiology.

The C-terminal region of lipin is critical for enzyme activity and also contains the acyl-CoA binding site. Lipin proteins are expressed in most tissues, in particular in adipose tissue, and have been shown to be involved in the regulation of lipid metabolism. Lipins are serine/threonine kinases that are involved in regulating pathways that control lipid homeostasis, including triglycerides, fatty acids, and phospholipids. Lipins are also involved in the regulation of signaling pathways that control cell proliferation, apoptosis, and inflammation.

The human lipin gene family is composed of 6 genes. Lipin-1 is expressed ubiquitously in most adult tissues. Lipin-2 is highly expressed in the brain, whereas lipin-3 and lipin-5 are expressed in adipose tissue. Lipin-4 is expressed in the heart, whereas lipin-6 and lipin-7 are expressed in lung tissue. Lipin-1 and lipin-3 are able to transfer acyl groups from acyl-CoA to phosphatidic acid and lysophosphatidic acid. Lipin-2 can transfer acyl groups from acyl-CoA to a wide variety of lipid substrates. Lipin-1, lipin-2, and lipin-3 have been shown to be important in regulating the metabolic pathways that control triglyceride synthesis and lipid droplet formation in lipid-laden cells. Lipin-1 is activated by phosphorylation by lipin-2 in response to insulin.

My biggest problem with lean manufacturing is the non-labor resource -
automation. Lean manufacturing is a lazy man's way of automating factories.

The other problem is that lean manufacturing is just a poorly defined term.

For retrieving messages, IMAP (which replaced the older POP3) is standard, but proprietary servers also often implement proprietary protocols.

To be honest, I thought this drink was a bit of a fail. I would be more interested in a margarita made with tequila or scotch than the stuff from the bottle. But it was a nice way to use up the bottle of tequila that I bought. My son wanted to try it again, and I thought since it was a quick and easy recipe, I would share it with him. I am glad I did, it was really tasty! It was tasty with some fresh lime juice and salt. My son liked it with salt and some lime juice. I thought that it would be a nice way to use up the tequila in the bottle. You could make it with regular or triple sec tequila, or any other type of alcohol. The recipe below is for regular tequila. You can use any type of alcohol.

Mix:In a small pitcher pour about 1/4 of the tequila and mix with a spoon. Add a little more tequila until you have a good amount of liquid.

Pour:In a glass measure add about 2 ounces of the remaining tequila. Stir until it is fully mixed in.

Lemon Zest:Cut the lemon in half and scoop out the juice. Add the juice to the pitcher. Add the lemon zest to the pitcher.

Lime Juice:Add the juice of 3 limes to the pitcher.

Salt:Add a little salt to the pitcher.

Stir: Stir the pitcher until it is fully mixed in.

Serve:Serve the margarita in a glass with a straw. Add a lime wedge or wedge of lemon to the glass.

For the sake of the recipe, I added a little salt, lime juice, and lemon zest to this drink. You can add whatever flavorings you want to this drink.

This is a simple recipe that can be made as long as you have fresh lime juice, salt, tequila, and a pitcher.

National Financial Switch (NFS) is the largest network of shared automated teller machines (ATMs) in India. It was designed, developed and deployed by the Institute for Development and Research in Banking Technology (IDRBT) in 2004, with the goal of inter-connecting the ATMs in the country and facilitating convenience banking. It is run by the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI). As on 31st January’ 22, there were 1,203 members that includes 111 Direct, 1,045 Sub members, 43 RRBs and 4 WLAOs using NFS network connected to more than 2.55 Lac ATM (including cash deposit machines/recyclers).
The National Financial Switch was launched by the IDRBT on 27 August 2004, connecting the ATMs of three banks, Corporation Bank, Bank of Baroda and ICICI Bank.The IDRBT then worked towards bringing all major banks in India on board and by December 2009, the network had grown to connect 49,880 ATMs of 37 banks, thereby emerging as the largest network of shared ATMs in the country.

Rathore received the title of "Rathore" from his father, Holkar. The

Holkar's aunt, Jotiba, was Holkar's mother, and Holkar's mother was the

Holkar's mother was the sister of Holkar's grandfather, Sindhia. Sindhia

input: Running a business is tough and there will always be problems in the market.  Make the case to a skeptical colleague as to why private sector managers should devote attention and energy to being a steward of the institutions of capitalism. Please include citations for Jonathan Haidt.
output:
ation is a major economic and social problem, and its solution requires the attention of many people. Please include citations for Paul Graham.

A:

I think the best way to approach this is to say that the only way we can be sure that the modern economy will work is to have a large sample of the population that are willing to pay for it.  If a large enough majority can't afford to pay for a given service, we may have a problem.
For example, suppose that most people have the opposite opinion of you or me, that we are being paid to do a certain task.  I have a rather large sample of people willing to pay me to do a certain task, but for most people my opinion is not worth much.  If the majority of people who thought I was being paid to do the task had found me, I would be toast.  I am convinced that we need to have a large enough sample of people willing to pay for a particular job that the majority of those who think it is worth something are willing to pay for it.  If I have a sample of people willing to pay me for a task, but most people don't think I'm worth it, I am toast.
I think the same is true of the economy as a whole.  People with an opinion that it is worth investing in the market economy can be convinced that it is worth investing in the market economy, and if they can convince themselves that it is worth investing in the market economy, the market economy will grow and prosper.

I believe that answer to be business leaders themselves -- or else be beholden to government regulation to steward the institution in the direction that benefits not just owners and shareholders, but all stakeholders including employees and the environment.

His photographs were made possible by the invention of the 35mm film camera, the advent of the motorcar and the personal camera. They are not only beautiful to look at but they are timeless.

He was used to travelling by stagecoach, but his first motorcar was a gift from an admirer. He bought a camera, and began to travel around the West. He was soon joined by his brother Norman, who also became a photographer. Adams first photographed Yosemite. Later he explored the northern reaches of Alaska, and his photographs of the Yukon were praised by Ernest Thompson Seton as being the best in the world. There are many types of software pricing models, but broadly they can be divided into three categories: perpetual, subscription, and consumption.

Perpetual software pricing models, also known as perpetual licensing models, allow the software to be purchased for a one-time fee.  Typically the buyer has nearly unlimited use of the software in perpetuity.  If updates to the software are required, a separate software maintenance package may be purchased.

Subscription software allows unlimited use of the software for a predetermined period, often 1 year or 3 years, for a price.  Updates to the software are often included in the price of the subscription.  At the end of the subscription term, the buyer usually has the option to renew their subscription.

Consumption-based software allows the buyer to pay for their actual usage of the software during a period of time, for example monthly.  In this type of arrangement, the actual usage can vary from period to period, resulting in customer charges that vary as well.  Some customers like knowing that they will only pay for what they use, while other customers dislike the unpredictability of their bills.

GWA studies typically focus on associations between single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) and traits like major human diseases, but can equally be applied to any other genetic variants and any other organisms.

When applied to human data, GWA studies compare the DNA of participants having varying phenotypes for a particular trait or disease. These participants may be people with a disease (cases) and similar people without the disease (controls), or they may be people with different phenotypes for a particular trait, for example blood pressure. This approach is known as phenotype-first, in which the participants are classified first by their clinical manifestation(s), as opposed to genotype-first. Each person gives a sample of DNA, from which millions of genetic variants are read using SNP arrays. The integration language is based on the ISO 10303-3 standard and is used to integrate the process-system and the subprocesses.

A:

The typical way to read a financial statement is as a snapshot of "what happened" during the financial year.
The year starts on 1 January, and is divided into twelve months.
The statement is divided into two sections. The first section shows how the company's assets, and the equity of the owner, have changed during the year. The second shows how the company's liabilities have changed.
An asset is anything that can be sold (or could be sold, or has been sold) for money. For example, a company can have an asset of a building, or an asset of a computer, or an asset of a company car.
An owner owns an asset, and a company has several owners, each owning a share in the company. The owner of a share in a company owns a share of the assets of that company.
So the first line of a financial statement shows how the assets of the company, and the owners of the company, have changed.
The second line of the financial statement shows how the liabilities of the company, and the owners of the company, have changed.
A company doesn't have to have money flowing through it (or assets of any kind) to earn a profit. If the company sells a good for money, it earns a profit. If the company pays a bill for money, and pays interest on the money, the company earns a profit. And if the company pays a bill for money and pays a dividend, the company earns a profit.
A company can also earn a profit by earning money in other ways, such as by selling goods, or by investing money, or by borrowing money from others.
A business' profits are divided into two parts. The first part is called shareholders' profits. The shareholders of the company own a share of the profits.
The second part is called non-shareholders' profits. This part includes all the profits not owned by the shareholders.
A business can also earn a profit by paying dividends to its shareholders.
If a business pays dividends to its shareholders, the shareholders get money. If a business doesn't pay dividends, the shareholders don't get money.
If a business pays a dividend to shareholders, this is called a dividend payment.
Dividends are paid to shareholders by companies at certain times.
A dividend is a payment to a shareholder of money.

label:
The stock market helps companies raise money to fund operations by selling shares of stock, and it creates and sustains wealth for individual investors.

Companies raise money on the stock market by selling ownership stakes to investors. These equity stakes are known as shares of stock. By listing shares for sale on the stock exchanges that make up the stock market, companies get access to the capital they need to operate and expand their businesses without having to take on debt. In exchange for the privilege of selling stock to the public, companies are required to disclose information and give shareholders a say in how their businesses are run.

Investors benefit by exchanging their money for shares on the stock market. As companies put that money to work growing and expanding their businesses, investors reap the benefits as their shares of stock become more valuable over time, leading to capital gains. In addition, companies pay dividends to their shareholders as their profits grow.

The performances of individual stocks vary widely over time, but taken as a whole the stock market has historically rewarded investors with average annual returns of around 10%, making it one of the most reliable ways of growing your money.

label: Oxidation reduction potential or ORP is measurement for water.  A millivolt meter can measure ORP and it is a measure of the potential of water to carry or hold antioxidants.  It is not a guarantee of antioxidants in water.  One form of antioxidants in water is free floating dissolved hydrogen.  A good analogy of antioxidants in water is the following: ORP is like a big swimming pool of potential but at the moment its currently empty and dissolved hydrogen is like ball of finite size.  The larger the ORP'swimming pool' the more dissolved hydrogen 'balls' can fit in that pool.  An ORP with a large negative value is huge swimming pool, and an OPR with a high positive value is no swimming pool.  ORP can also measure whether water is acidic or alkaline.  ORP that is negative tends more toward alkaline water, and ORP which is positive tends more towards neutral water and acidic water.

ter's Oct 12, 2014 #05 I have been using OKRs for several years at my current company and it has been a great success. My team meets with me once a month to discuss how we are progressing and, based on that, we make our OKRs. What I like about it is that it gives us the opportunity to discuss and share our progress with each other. It also gives us the chance to share any concerns we might have with each other that the OKR doesn't cover. There's no one best approach to OKRs, though. Use what works well for your team. I am currently a consultant that works with other startups on OKRs, and we have a very different approach to the process. My approach is more about setting goals and tracking progress than it is about getting everyone on the same page. It's about productivity and common sense, not about OKRs. Let's get to work. Oct 12, 2014 #03 I am in the process of forming an OKR team at my company and would like to solicit the opinions of those who have done this before. I do not have a business background or any experience with OKRs. I am hoping that some of you can suggest some good practices that you have used in the past and share your experiences. Oct 12, 2014 #02 It's definitely a team process, though I would also think that it is a team responsibility to set goals and objectives. It's not a one-man show. I have seen a few OKRs on this forum, and they're all very similar. A couple of them have a fairly detailed list of OKR items, including a budget for each category. What happens in the event of a team member who doesn't meet their goals? I see this as a good opportunity to get them to understand that it is important to set goals. I personally have never seen a team member say, "I don't have time to do OKR." They might feel that they don't have time, but a lot of them would. label: Developing OKRs for your team is a useful way to identify what goals your team will focus on and provide specific, time-bound metrics you can use to measure your success. First, identify the most important objectives for your organization - usually no more than five. Next, identify your Key Results. These Key Results should follow the SMART principles. They should be Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound. Once you have identified both your objectives and key results, share them with your team for their input. Once you have collected that input, finalize your OKRs and roll them out to the team through the appropriate communications channel.

output: For this recipe, you can use one of the following potatoes:* Yukon gold potatoes (or their French name, paupiettes) would make a great base for this recipe. Yukon gold potatoes have a mild flavor, so they're great for dishes like this one, and they can be used in salads and soups, or even as a side dish for cheese dishes. I like to use Yukon Golds because they're not as starchy as russets and they're more tender and easier to carve.Shredded potatoes also work well, but russets are a little more starchy. They have a slight chewier texture that's more characteristic of potatoes. The "starchiness" of potatoes is a matter of how much or how little moisture they're exposed to when they're cut. When you cut potatoes, the moisture they contain is released into the air, and it can get trapped in the cut. If they're exposed to too much moisture, they'll hold it too tightly in the cut and become starchy. If they're exposed to too little moisture, they'll hold it too loosely in the cut and become rubbery.Healthy potatoes "starchier" than their starchy cousins, russets, are sometimes referred to as "steaming potatoes" because they'll steam up if you leave them in a pan for too long. These potatoes are great when they're cooked in water with a pinch of sea salt added to them. Potatoes, like most foods, will have a mild taste if they come from a healthy source, but if they're over-processed, they'll carry a stronger taste.If you use russets, you can use them as a base for this recipe, but you'll need to grate them yourself, or you can use the bagged potato slices you get at the supermarket. The trouble with this is that the way we consume media today for marketing is very different from the way it was in the past, and that the way we consume media today will probably change even more in the future. It will be increasingly difficult to determine the real value of a product or service that is only being shown to a few dozen people or even less.

I can understand this difficulty, but there are ways to mitigate it. I have no problem with the idea of measuring the value of a product or service that is being shown to a large audience, even if I am not sure how many people are actually seeing it.

The trouble is that the way we measure the value of advertising today is not the same as the way it was when the first ad was run in a newspaper. Advertising has changed in both the technology it uses and the platform it is displayed on. It has changed in the medium in which it is delivered, but it has also changed in the way it is measured.

For example, the number of times an ad is displayed has changed. Displayed on a website, the ad typically gets seen by far fewer people than it would if it were displayed on a billboard or on the side of a bus. The number of times an ad is viewed has also changed. Advertisers are increasingly using the power of algorithms to target advertising to people who are most likely to be interested in a particular product or service.

In short, the measurements we use to determine the value of advertising have changed, and it is very difficult to determine the value of a product or service that is only being shown to a few dozen people or even less.

I will be the first to admit that I am not an expert on measuring advertising value. But I do know that many businesses and organizations are failing to measure or understand the value of their marketing. This is what I want to talk about (and why I started the measurement challenge), so I want to understand what the measurement of advertising is like today.

Websites and Advertising

One very popular reason is they feel great pride in seeing their children grow into adulthood and take on the responsibility of having children. A second reason grandparents say their role is so special is they get to enjoy their grandchildren, and then return them to their parents who have the ongoing responsibility for raising the children. This creates a special bond between the grandparents and grandchildren that many grandparents describe as special.  A third reason many say it is special to be a grandparent is tied to an instinctive love they describe that they have for their grandchildren. The primary mode of transportation across the San Francisco bay prior to the Golden Gate Bridge was by water. This was a direct consequence of the Bay Area's geography. The bay is a deep basin, surrounded by hills. The hills would have served to shield any ship that traversed the bay from the direct effects of fog, or strong winds.
The floor of the bay is only a few feet above sea level, leaving the bay below it - free of hills, and thus exposed to the effects of strong winds. Therefore, ships were required to travel around the bay to reach the water below it, which is at a much lower elevation than the Bay itself.
The first ship to traverse the bay was the Baltimore, built in 1790. It was built with a deck on both sides of the ship, which allowed for cargo to be unloaded aft, and cargo to be loaded forward. This allowed the ship to sail in a straight line along the bay. By the time the first ship was built, the bay was a military port, so the cargo was primarily military supplies, and the ship was designed to carry a maximum number of soldiers.

input: Explain gravity
label:
Gravity is a fundamental interaction which causes mutual attraction between all things with mass or energy. Gravity is the weakest of the four fundamental interactions namely the strong, weak, electromagnetic and gravity. However, it is the most significant interaction between objects at the macroscopic scale, and it determines the motion of planets, stars, galaxies, and even light. 
Gravity is most accurately described by the general theory of relativity that was proposed by Albert Einstein. The theory describes gravity not as a force, but as the curvature of spacetime, caused by the uneven distribution of mass, and causing masses to move along geodesic lines.
However, for most applications, gravity is well approximated by Newton's law of universal gravitation, which describes gravity as a force causing any two bodies to be attracted toward each other, with magnitude proportional to the product of their masses and inversely proportional to the square of the distance between them.

Ah, distinctly I remember it was in the bleak December;
And each separate dying ember wrought its ghost upon the floor.
Eagerly I wished the morrow;—vainly I had sought to borrow
From my books surcease of sorrow—sorrow for the lost Lenore—
For the rare and radiant maiden whom the angels name Lenore—
Nameless here for evermore.

The idea behind Scala is that it is an object-oriented language, but this doesn't mean that everything in Scala is object-oriented.
From the Scala documentation:

Scala is an object-oriented language, but it's not a full-fledged object-oriented language. That's because Scala is designed to run on the JVM and Java's standard API. In Scala, methods and variables are first-class values, and classes are mostly syntactic sugar for object definitions.

In particular, the build system is not an object-oriented language.

input: Identify which animal is domesticated or wild: Horse, Red deer
output:
, Red foxFox, Rabbit, Dog, Cattle, Pig, Goat, etc.

SOCIETIES

Societies are groups of animals that are similar in many ways, and are usually part of a single species. Societies have social and mating systems, and are governed by either a single group or several groups. Societies vary in size from small, ungulate societies such as deer and rabbits, to large, mammal-like societies such as horse-owning societies or human societies. Societies can be divided into three types of groups: closed, semi-closed and open.

Closed societies
Closed societies are societies with no external contact except contacts with other members of the society. Each member of the society knows the identity of every member. Members can only meet in certain places, and have no access to the outside world. These societies are the largest in the animal kingdom, and include societies such as the wolf pack, the eagle society, the crow society, the porcupine society, and the cougar society.

Semi-closed societies
Semi-closed societies have moderate contact with the outside world. Members of the society can be known, but do not know the identity of every member. They are usually large and complex. These societies include societies such as the horse society, the fish society, the elephant society, the baboon society, and the bear society.

Open societies
Open societies can be divided into two major types, in which the society is open to outsiders or not. Societies that are open to outsiders are usually small and close. Societies that are not open to outsiders are usually large and complex. These societies include the lion society, the elephant society, the lemur society, the primate society, and the human society.

Prince Rogers Nelson (June 7, 1958 – April 21, 2016), commonly known mononymously as Prince, was an American singer, songwriter, musician, and record producer. The recipient of numerous awards and nominations, he is widely regarded as one of the greatest musicians of his generation.
He was known for his flamboyant, androgynous persona; his wide vocal range, which included a far-reaching falsetto and high-pitched screams; and his skill as a multi-instrumentalist, often preferring to play all or most of the instruments on his recordings.
Prince produced his albums himself, pioneering the Minneapolis sound. His music incorporated a wide variety of styles, including funk, R&B, rock, new wave, soul, synth-pop, pop, jazz, and hip hop.

Business Process Mapping describes the capture of a set of business activities that deliver an outcome.  Mapping is usually performed using visual tools that use standardized shapes to indicate entities.  Mapping involves capturing activities, the roles performing the activities, systems and tools used to execute the activities and inputs and outputs from the activities.  Process mapping is frequently conducted in cross functional workshops with a facilitator capturing the activities performed by Subject Matter Experts (SMEs).  Common uses of process mapping include:
* automation
* compliance documentation
* business process improvement
* standardization

The Sydney Opera House is a multi-venue performing arts centre in Sydney. Located on the foreshore of Sydney Harbour, it is widely regarded as one of the world's most famous and distinctive buildings and a masterpiece of 20th-century architecture.

Designed by Danish architect Jorn Utzon, but completed by an Australian architectural team headed by Peter Hall, the building was formally opened by Queen Elizabeth II on 20 October 1973 after a gestation beginning with Utzon's 1957 selection as winner of an international design competition. The Government of New South Wales, led by the premier, Joseph Cahill, authorised work to begin in 1958 with Utzon directing construction. The government's decision to build Utzon's design is often overshadowed by circumstances that followed, including cost and scheduling overruns as well as the architect's ultimate resignation.

The building and its surrounds occupy the whole of Bennelong Point on Sydney Harbour, between Sydney Cove and Farm Cove, adjacent to the Sydney central business district and the Royal Botanic Gardens, and near to the Sydney Harbour Bridge.

Cue the dreaded "I'm not a parent" line. I'm sitting here waiting for it to happen; it probably won't. But it's likely to come up in conversations about kids. And it's possibly a topic on the agenda for therapy.

I've written before about how I am afraid of being a parent. I don't know why. Maybe because I don't want to be responsible for someone else's life, I don't know, or maybe because I just don't think I'm in the right headspace to be a parent.

I have to say that I'm not sure I've ever been a parent. I've been in a few relationships, but never a parenting one. I've been married to a couple of people who were OK with parenting, but never one who was obviously in the trenches with that.

And I'm not the only one. I know that lots of people in the parenting community are, as I am, of the opinion that child-rearing is a tough gig. But I don't think that's a fact.

If you ask me, the truth is that parenting is not a tough gig. It's really, really easy. If you think about it, you'll realize that.

I used to watch a lot of TV shows about raising kids, and what I learned was that it takes very little work to raise a happy, healthy, productive child.

In fact, if you think about it, parenting is really not all that different from other things that we do every day. It's just a matter of taking care of yourself.

This is why I've always thought it was bizarre that parenting is so often discussed as if it were a job.

I'm not going to tell you that you can be a parent and you just "get it." I'm not going to tell you that if you're a parent you know what you're doing.

I'm going to tell you that parenting is really, really easy. And that you don't have to be a parent to know what you're doing.

How do I know? Because I'm a parent.

But I'm also a writer. And that means I write about parenting. And that means I'm writing about how easy parenting is.

What are some useful ways to repurpose a cardboard box?

I'm using a cardboard box for my doggie bed and I'm trying to figure out a way to use the cardboard box as storage, but I also need the inside of the box to be dry and free of moisture. Any suggestions?

A:

Cardboard boxes are great for storage.  Even better if they're made of wood, like the ones you see at the local lumberyard.  Most cardboard boxes are made of paper.  Paper is a good insulator, so it's good for storing things that don't require a lot of airflow.  
If you're trying to dry the inside of the box out so it's not wet, you could try to use a fan to blow air into the box, or to run a hose from outside into the box and just use a hose to spray the inside of the box with water.  
A second option is to use a plastic bag or something similar to seal the inside of the box.  You can use a small amount of water to seal the outside of the box, and then fill it with dryer sheets, potato chip bags, or the like to keep the inside dry.  This will take a little bit of extra work, but will be a lot more efficient.

As at the 2001 census, the population of Mayfield Park of East Bristol was 11,648. Mayfield Park of East Bristol has a station on the Bristol Orbital Railway, whose line is part of the wider Bristol Orbital network. Mayfield Park station is on the Orbital's line from Kingswood to Bitton.

input: What are some ways I can improve my general health during my work day?
output:
Weekly

Working conditions can be quite stressful, but your body has to cope with it somehow. Stress is a physiological response to any kind of threat, and so it's important to nurture and protect our bodies at the workplace.

The following tips may help you maintain good health as you work.

1. Eat healthfully

Eating healthfully is important at the office, so make sure you're eating a balanced diet, including protein.

If you can't eat a healthy diet, eat smaller meals to keep your energy up.

2. Get plenty of sleep

If you're stressed at the office, you may find that you need more sleep. Sleep can be difficult to get at work, but it can be quite beneficial to your health.

When you're stressed, your body goes into fight-or-flight mode. This means that your body will prepare for the fight or flight. If you are in a fight-or-flight mode, and your body is not getting enough sleep, you may be vulnerable to illness, fatigue, and injury.

If you do not get enough sleep, you may find it hard to perform at your best. Even if you do not need to sleep, make sure you get enough.

3. Stretch regularly

If you're working out in the office, you may need to stretch at least two or three times a week. Stretching releases tension in muscles, which can help your body function more effectively.

Stretching also helps you relax, which can help you work more productively.

4. Get enough fluids

Dry, salty, and warm foods may make you more prone to illness and fatigue.

Drink enough water throughout the day. Make sure you drink water with meals, and drink enough during the day to avoid dehydration.

5. Stay active

Staying active can help you stay healthy at the office. Regular exercise can help you relax, relieve stress, and get rid of tension.

If you're able to, take the stairs instead of the elevator. If you are in an office where others are working, work out in a different part of the building. Go for a walk, or jog.

6. Take breaks

input: What are the parts of a sail?
output: Medieval shipbuildingSails have the important function of propulsion, but also have an important decorative role. They can be composed of various materials such as canvas, kevlar, and even wood. The following topics describe the parts and construction of a sail.Parts of a sail.The sail assembles from a series of thin, flexible sheets.Each of the sheets has a hand-sewn or machine-sewn seam, which is sewn in an overlapping fashion along the length of the sail. The seams are actually sewn in such a way that they do not have to be fastened, but instead are held in place by the tension of the sail itself. Only a small number of loose sailmaker’s stitches separate the seams, and this number is generally only one per seam.The material of the sail is the single most important factor in how well the sail works. Diverse types of fabric are used in different types of ships. Sailmakers can choose from a variety of different cloths, such as canvas, hemp, and sea-grass. The canvas sail is the most common on traditional, sail-powered ships. Other types of cloths are used, for example, on early, sailing ships. The cloths are joined together using a variety of methods, including sewing, lacing, and braiding. The most common method is to stitch the cloths together, usually with a single stitch per seam. This method is also sometimes referred to as “hand-sewing.” The yardage of the sail is adjusted by the sailmaker, typically by sewing additional cleats or tack stitches along the length of the sail. The sailmaker also adjusts the shape of the sail to conform to the different conditions.Sail strength and construction.A sail is stitched to a mast (the upper part of a mast that can be raised or lowered independently of the main mast). The mast is held in place by the sail, and the mast is connected to the ship’s deck through the deck rigging. The mast and the sail are made of wood, and the two are usually connected by a crossbar. The sail is stitched to the mast from the bottom up, so that the sail begins at the bottom of the mast. The sailmaker then staples or nailed the sail to the mast for strength.As a sail is stitched to the mast, a single line of stitching runs between the two. This single line of stitching is called the “foresail line.”
label: The parts of a sail are: Head, Leech, Clew, Foot, Tack, and Luff.

: Self-improvement is a part of the mountain lifestyle, and I don’t think I’ve ever been better at bouldering and climbing than right now.

How to Boulder? (For Newbies)

By Chris Bunkers

Bouldering is much more than just climbing a boulder. As I climb and boulder, my strategy is always the same: I learn to listen to my body, and I listen to my body by paying attention to my heart rate and breathing.

The first thing I always do when I start a climb is listen to my heart rate. I’ve found that I need to be at a relatively low heart rate to climb, so I try to keep my heart rate slow and steady. If I’m climbing with a friend, I’ll listen to my pulse in my ear, and my buddy will also listen to his heart rate. I find that listening to your pulse and heart rate can help you learn to pay attention to your body in a way that is completely different from just listening to your heart rate and breathing.

Bouldering is all about learning to listen to your body, which is not something you can do by just listening to your heart rate and breathing. I’ve learned that listening to my heart rate is a good way to get a baseline for what my heart rate will be while I climb. All the way up to a harder, more difficult climb, I listen to my heart rate with a watch or a GPS, but I’m learning that I can listen to my heart rate with my body even when I’m climbing.

The next thing I always do when I start a climb is listen to my heart rate. I use a watch or GPS to listen to my heart rate, but I also listen to my heart rate with my body. The cool thing about listening to your heart rate with your body is that you can listen to it with everything you’re doing.

I check my heart rate every time I get on a chairlift, even when I’m standing. I listen to my heart rate when I’m hiking, and I even listen to my heart rate while I’m climbing. I listen to my heart rate while I’m sitting on my couch, while I’m getting my hair cut, while I’m watching TV. I listen to it while I’m eating dinner. I listen to my heart rate when I’m getting ready to sleep.

input: What are some former names for the city of Mumbai?
output: ferrumMumbai is the capital of the India state of Maharashtra and the largest city in the country, with a population of about 21.5 million. It is also one of the most densely populated urban areas in the world, owing to its location at the mouth of the Ganga and its trade routes.Mumbai was formerly known by both its English and Sanskrit names: Bombay, or Khandesh, and Mahabalipuram. The city was once known as Khandesh (Khandesh), meaning "the land of the Khandes". It derives from the Sanskrit कंडेस्ट, or "city of the Khandes", a reference to the Khandes, a group of small Hindu kings who ruled the area in the 9th and 10th centuries.Mumbai is one of the most heavily urbanised cities in the world, with more than 60% of the population living in urban areas. The city's population has grown from 1.4 million in 1950 to over 20 million in the present, and is projected to reach over 30 million by 2050. Mumbaikars are known as "the most cosmopolitan people in India", with over 500 different languages understood and spoken in the city.The city's name is derived from the Sanskrit words महाबाद, meaning "the end of the sea", and मङ्गा, meaning "the city". Mahabalipuram, a small town in the vicinity of the city, was the capital of the former state of Pemmarajupattanagar, and its name was given to the city by the British on the advice of Pemba Tahr, who visited the place on his way to Pune. The area's name was later changed to Mumbai. The name "Mumbai" is believed to have first appeared in English literature in the early 20th century, when it appeared in several popular novels, notably The Adventures of Pinocchio by Carlo Collodi.

input: What is the difference between a fire fighter and a nurse?
output:

A fire fighter is someone who puts out fires and a nurse is someone who treats patients.

Nurses are a subset of medical technicians. Medical technicians provide medical care to patients, but are not doctors.
label: A fire fighter is responsible for responding to emergencies that are mostly related to fires. A typical task would be to ride in a fire truck from the fire station to a home that has caught fire and use water and other fire-fighting tools to put it out. Simple moving average: This involves taking the average of a certain number of past data points, and using it as the forecast for the next period. This method can be effective for stable time series with no trend or seasonality.

In mathematics and computer science, an optimisation problem is typically a search problem in which the best solution is to locate among all feasible solutions. An optimisation problem can be categorised as continuous or discrete depending on the type of their variables. In a discrete optimisation problem, variables are discrete and countable. In contrast, continuous variables include infinitely uncountable values, for example, a variable over a non-empty range of real numbers. 

According to the number of objective functions, an optimisation problem is classified as single or multi-objective. A single-objective optimisation problem only involves one objective function to optimise. On the other hand, a multi-objective one considers two or more objectives simultaneously, which means the interaction between objectives has to be considered.

There is no single component that we are just going to focus on in this article. Kubernetes clusters are composed of nodes, each of which acts as an independent control plane. In other words, each control plane has the ability to act on its own. In Kubernetes, each control plane is called a *controller*. The controllers combine to form the *control plane*. A controller's responsibilities include orchestrating the control plane, providing a virtual network, managing the network load balancing and providing a virtual IP address for the entire cluster.

*Control plane* is a configuration management approach for deploying applications (e.g., microservices) in a cluster. For example, applications can be deployed using a single controller or multiple controllers. In a cluster where each controller is managing an independent cluster, the design is called *decentralized*.

A *decentralized control plane* allows you to deploy applications in an independent manner. In a cluster in which each controller is managing a cluster, the design is called *centralized control plane*.

The Kubernetes architecture is built on the control plane. It is composed of:

-   **Apps**: pods that are the source of traffic. When a pod is created, it automatically creates a number of pods.

input: Can you write a brief summary for the book "Braving the Wilderness" by Brene Brown?
output:
ation of the Human Spirit

A:

How to think about your self-talk

A:

When you begin to feel you are "losing" your mind, I would encourage you to take a step back and reflect on what you are thinking about in the moment.
Consider:

What are the thoughts that are running through your mind?
Are you focusing on those thoughts or are you engaging with the world around you?
What is your purpose in this moment?
What is your intention in this moment?

And if you're not sure of what to do, take a moment to write down the answer to each of those questions.  Then, write down another question to ask yourself:

What do I need to do to be happy?
What do I need to do to feel good about myself?
What do I need to do to feel good about my life?

Ask yourself those questions until they start to feel "natural."
Also, you can ask yourself:

Is this feeling in line with who I am and what I want?
If it is, do I need to change it?

If you're not sure of what to do, take a moment to write down the answer to each of those questions.  Then, write down another question to ask yourself:

What do I need to do to be happy?
What do I need to do to feel good about myself?
What do I need to do to feel good about my life?

Ask yourself those questions until they start to feel "natural."
Then, what you need to do is to find a way to let go of your self-talk.  How do I do that?  I think just by taking a moment to focus on your breathing and be in the moment.
Because when you are in the moment, you won't think about all of the things that are going on around you.  You are able to be in the moment because you are not trying to control it.

A core idea is that if you are courageous enough to stand alone in the name of the virtues and values you believe in, you can actually create more belonging for others. To brave the wilderness is not to go into the woods armored and ready to fight, but with an open heart and conviction steadying your spine.

input: Given this paragraph about Chief Uncas, who was he?
output:
, the father of Pocasset and Monadnock.

"On the other side of the Long Island Sound from Pocasset, where the Island is said to be, stands a hamlet called Monadnock, in which lived a man of a name now unknown, but of whom you have heard in these pages, a young man of noble spirit and excellent qualities, who was much beloved by the people of the place. Monadnock was rich in a great many natural productions, and was famous for his skill as a hunter. But, it happened that his life was passed in a state of great neglect, with only a few of his relations and friends. At length it came to his ears that the chief Uncas had sent word to his people to come to him, that he had a great mass of property in the Island, and that he would be very glad to see them there.

"Monadnock was persuaded by the words of his friend and cousin Uncas. He came to the Island, and saw the length of the land and the beauty of the dwellings, as well as the great abundance of poultry and other animals, and the rich meadows and fields. He was delighted with all, and was very well pleased with the place. But his heart was greatly affected by seeing a young man of noble qualities, who had been so long neglected and buried in obscurity. He therefore said to himself, 'It will be well to build a temple for him, and call him to be the chief of the Island; and this, in time, may be the means of his being raised into fame.' So he built a temple, and called him to be the chief. And this man was known to the people of the Island, by the name of the chief Pocasset.

"For a year or two he was very happy, and the people of the Island were very well pleased with him. But the time came when they began to be afraid of him. They feared that the chief was growing proud, and that he would get a great many followers, and that they would be obliged to send him away. But they were not ashamed to say so, because they had heard that the chief Uncas was already very rich, and had many followers. So they sent Uncas a message, saying, 'If the chief Pocasset has many followers, we would be glad to see them; but we will not send him away because we are afraid of his pride.'
label: Uncas (c. 1588 – c. 1683) was a sachem of the Mohegans who made the Mohegans the leading regional Indian tribe in lower Connecticut, through his alliance with the New England colonists against other Indian tribes.
